paragraph: Brian Willoughby (born 20 September 1949) is a British guitarist. He has worked with many musicians, notably Dave Cousins and The  Strawbs, Mary Hopkin, as well as releasing solo work.
Old School Songs – with Dave Cousins (1979)
Suspended Animation (The Monks) (UK band) (Gold Album in Canada 1981)
Other Voices, Too (A Trip Back to Bountiful) – Nanci Griffith (1998)
Full Bloom  – Acoustic Strawbs (2005) live at Natural Sound, Kitchener, Ontario, Canada (2004)
Live at the Royal Festival Hall – Mary Hopkin (2005)
St. Pancras Old Church, London + Cathryn CraigCountless other albums as session player – 1969 – present.
"Might as Well Be on Mars" – Strawbs (Canada 1991)
"Freeway To Her Dreams " - Freeway To Her Dreams  Written By Gordon Haskell
"Whole Wide World" – Cathryn Craig & Brian Willoughby, featuring Righteous Brother Bill Medley Written By Gordon HaskellCountless other singles as session player 1969 – present.
